# Sorting Algorithm Benchmark Results

## Basic Sorts (Week 1)
| Algorithm      | 500 Elements | 1000 Elements |
|----------------|--------------|---------------|
| Bubble Sort    | 0.00520s     | 0.02154s      |
| Selection Sort | 0.00206s     | 0.00883s      |
| Insertion Sort | 0.00209s     | 0.00899s      |

## Observations
- **Bubble Sort** was the slowest, taking significantly longer as the list size doubled.
- **Selection and Insertion** performed similarly on random data.
- All three algorithms show **O(n²)** growth (when the input size doubled, the time increased by roughly 4x).